item.title:
Sydney Cricket Ground precinct is expected to lift its concert limit cap from 4 per year to 20, to attract more global stars to perform in the city.
The cap has been blamed for stopping Sydney hosting artists like Beyoncé, Bon Jovi, Foo Fighters and Billy Joel.
